Wikimedia Commons has media related to Archives in Canada.

This list of archives in Canada contains archives which are understood for the purposes of this list as entities that work to acquire, preserve and make available material as documentary evidence about a person, community, business, government, municipality, etc. for future generations.[1] The types of archives categories - Business, Community, Cultural, Educational, Healthcare, Human Rights, Government, Military, Regional, Professional association, Religious, University/College, Sport, Arts - have been adapted from those used in the Archives Association of Ontario's Archeion.[2] Archives that exist only in digital form are not included.

To use the sortable table, click on the icons at the top of each column to sort that column in alphabetical order; click again for reverse alphabetical order.
